            <div class="grid-pattern" aria-hidden="true"></div>

            <div class="wrapper">
                <header>
                    <a href="/" class="logo">Vikram</a>
                    <nav>
                        <a href="#work">Work</a>
                        <a href="#writing">Writing</a>
                        <a href="#about">About</a>
                    </nav>
                </header>

                <main>
                    <section class="hero">
                        <div class="badges">
                            <span class="badge">Design Technologist</span>
                        </div>
                        <h1>Hey, I'm Vikram</h1>
                        <p class="hero-sub">
                            Frontend engineer building clean, fast web experiences — obsessing over the small details that make products feel right.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section class="section" id="about">
                        <div class="section-label">
                            <span class="dot"></span>
                            <span class="label-text">About</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            Most of my work lives in the frontend world — React, CSS, design systems, and tooling. I'm especially interested in intrinsic web design and letting the web do what it's good at.
